snippet.textDisplay:
Lol ok I love MMA but I see the MMA ego is getting way out of control here. Lets cover a few points here.
Number one is ESPN is the largest sports network in the world, it is the pinnacle of the UFC's achievements to be a part of it. You saying MMA fighters deserve more respect because they put their lives on the line has zero factual basis. More people have died from boxing and football injuries than MMA, number 2 the business perspective. UFC doesn't bring in nearly as much money as the NFL, not even close. Sooo yeah that whole "more respect thing", I think many will disagree.
Secondly this is entertainment, we can say wtf we want about it because wr are the ones paying for this last trash ppv. So I am going to. First off I know Cowboy didnt flop, he is a tough guy. With that being said I knew he wouldnt be competition for Conor and bet on Conor round 1 knockout. No disrespect to cowboy for his records and fight history, amazing stuff there. Yet big issue here, Cowboy has NEVER beaten anybody who was elite in this sport besides a very questionable decision to Benson Henderson years ago. He was in no way deserving of this fight, Gaethje smeared him and Tony soundly defeated him as well. You guys knew you were throwing Conor a bone... Three big fights for him potentially, there was Gaethje, Masvidal, and Cowboy. So he picked the only one on a losing streak over what Conor calls "A back and forth me and Donald have had for years". Is that so? I only remember one conversation that happened a half a decade ago and is in no way relevant. Sure good reason to give Conor an easy comeback. Thanks for the money btw Conor, that round 1 knockout was a no brainer.
I will finish it off like this, this is my opinion idgaf who doesn't like it or does. I pay to watch this garbage card that should have been a "fight night". If any professional fighter feels I am being disrespectful I also dont give a fukk. Time to stop acting like insecure babyd1cks if you get offended by fan critique. You're supposed to be professional fighters, tough guys. Start acting like it.
